Londen m. Henry Maynard
d
mij last to you was on the 23 sur. sence recd. yd of 12d. the reds & pack
whites are not yett arrived, I meane them that come ly tonwiel haveing no
news from him, though I much want them, as also the G.W. silver march H
cloathes, of which you must endeavour wish all expedition to dipatch 5 more
or elce itt will be impon for mee to keep the good fachers on my dand, surn
he is not so long a makeing them, or elce de delivers them to forne body
elce the 5 which he promised you, must be bere within 3 weekes to doguell
& then 5 more bere L august, & then5 more before £7d, & so collowing, because wee
shall bave ou att least of 25 p a yeare or 30 if wee will maintaine that concerne
so pray de yd. endeavour accordingly, I sare no more of the stametts I desired you to
spovide for a Ryall, & yett I am here asked for every day, & if that could take, I sha
have the opportunite to sell 50ƒ a yeace, then fore minde that I shall exspecs
the spanisch cloathes as soone as por pray putt in then 6 g. of whites ottou
hose for my wise, such as once you send mee before, cond that their cost be
brought to mij accct., & not other wise. yd. bill on me shall finde due complyance
suposeing itt is for mij acctt., of which you make no menhon, thelS I beliave is
sallen more at the latter end of ep. when you drew, because I have seen bill
of the same date att 35.5 & ul drawne on P ordaert. inclosed remitt you

a 29d.
oon m. Thomas Estabrock
I have recd. yd of 10 carts. as also oue fon m. Ledgingan of whom I had some times
a fort of 1½ yead white perpetuandos, which sort I never could have so well hom any other
Gand, because they must dave full that breack, & about 25 & weight aps. & be of
a substantall ware & cost not above 62 p ap which sort if you know not, m
ledgingain will tell you which itt is, for I would have no worse, butt rather much
better, & thicher ware theugh cas I told m. ledgingan I should give 5 a 6 p ap more
so if you please to send mee 12 f for a tryale, wee may see what wee shall do
more here after, for I have many goods yearry from yd parts, I am contented
I say to give 5 a 668p a p more for the perpeuancos, provided they be the better
accordingly so do yd endeavour, & ship them of att Topsom or epon by the first
that sailen, & I'll see you duely satssied, a word of anwe
